This paper proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation for image classification and semantic segmentation tasks using adversarial dropout regularization. The paper focuses on improving the discriminative features generated by the generator network, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
